C2 Matching Algorithm Enhancement_New HA: Test Case 1:Limit order with valid quotes and matching resting customer orders in the book. Start HALO Acution and No auction response. HALO will trade at CBOE There is no PMM in this case

Test Case 2:Limit order with valid quotes and matching resting customer orders in the book. HalO auction will start and order will trade at CBOE AUCTION RESPONSE will enter NBBO become worse than CBOE). Regualr allocation will takes place with PMM( 40%) and Price time allocation when the auction end

Test Case 3:Limit order with valid quotes and matching resting customer orders in the book. Start HALO acution and No acution response auction order will trade at CBOE. Acution Oder will trade allocate to Customer PMM (based on PMM allocation (50%))and then with Price Time

Test Case 4:Limit order with valid and matching resting customer order 1PMM 2 MM in the book. Hal will trade at CBOE START HAL NO AUCTION RESPONSE). Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation(40%) and then with Price Time

Test Case 5:Limit order with valid and matching price. 2 PMM in different price point and PMM 1 will trade in HALO(opening state and PMM allocation takes place and PMM 2 will trade after HAL auction end. 50 PMM allocation takes place in both side

Test Case 6:Limit order with valid and matching price 1PMM 1MM 1 customer order in the book. Hal will trade at CBOE START HAL NO AUCTION RESPONSE). Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation and then with Price Time before HAL and After HAL regular HAL trade will takes place. Hal will end without any HAL response. Two auction quies with different quantity

Test Case 7:Affliated firm has no auction response and 2MM 2MM and custoemr is booked in sell side before the auction starts(ordes came in pre open state). Auction will start at Buy side and Sell side orders will trade and get PDPM and Price time allocations(regular)

Test Case 8:Limit order with valid and matching price 2MM 2PMM 2 customer and a quote order in the book. After Hal aution ends trade will takes place at CBOE START HAL NO AUCTION RESPONSE). Auction order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation(40 and then with Price Time before HAL and After HAL regular HAL trade will takes place. Hal will end without any HAL response. One PMM will only get allocated price based on first in time sequence

Test Case 9:Limit order with valid and matching price 2MM 2PMM 2 customer order in the book. Hal will trade at CBOE START HAL NO AUCTION RESPONSE). Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation and then with Price Time before HAL and After HAL regular HAL trade will takes place. Hal will end without any HAL response. Both PMM will only get allocated price based on first in time sequence

Test Case 10:HalO will trade at CBOE START HALO and AUCTION RESPONSE will enter). HALO Auction will be end premeturely. Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation (50%)and then with Price Time

Test Case 11:Limit order with valid quotes and matching resting customer orders in the book. Hal will trade at CBOE START HAL NO AUCTION RESPONSE). Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation (50%)and then with Price Time

Test Case 12:Enter quote like order during HALO Auction CBOE becomes NBBO and trades with updated cboe quote Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation (50%)and then with Price Time

Test Case 13:Limit order with valid and matching price. 2 PMM in different price point and PMM 1 will trade in HALO(opening state and PMM allocation takes place and PMM 2 will trade after HAL auction end. 50 PMM allocation takes place in both side

Test Case 14:Enter a Non quote Like order during HALO auction CBEO becomes NBBO and Trades with ipdate cboe Quote. AON IOrder an pdpm MM orders will entered and booked in preopening state. After auction completed it will be traded according to PDPM allocation(40%)

Test Case 15:Limit order with valid and matching price. 2 PMM in different price point and PMM 1 will trade in HALO(opening state and PMM allocation takes place and PMM 2 will trade after HAL auction end. 50 PMM allocation takes place in both side

Test Case 16:Limit order with valid quotes and matching resting customer orders in the book. Hal will trade at CBOE START HAL NO AUCTION RESPONSE). Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation (50%)and then with Price Time

Test Case 17:Enter quote like order during HALO Auction CBOE becomes NBBO and trades with updated cboe quote Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation (40%)and then with Price Time. Incomming I order will not get any allocations

Test Case 18:Enter non quote like order during HALO Auction CBOE becomes NBBO and trades with updated cboe quote Incomming order will trade with Customer PMM based on PMM allocation (50%)and then with Price Time. Incomming C order will get allocations
Test Case 19:Inbound CBOE Quote same side of auction is better than NBBO during HAK Auction. Acution premeturely ends and trades with away exchange
